Reasoning: The paper deals with the (claw,diamond)-free Edge Deletion problem, which is a graph parameterization problem. This problem is related to graph theory, combinatorics, and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the characterization of (claw,diamond)-free graphs as line graphs of triangle-free graphs and as linear dominoes, which are topics related to graph theory and combinatorics. Hence, cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are also possible sub-categories.
